                "Description": "<section itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Organization\">\n  <h2 itemprop=\"name\">EFG Finance Division</h2>\n  <p itemprop=\"description\">The EFG Finance division serves as the central hub for financial operations and strategy. Its purpose is to streamline internal workflows, ensure consistency across the department, and provide a single source of truth for financial policies, standard operating procedures (SOPs), and strategic documentation. The division is dedicated to maintaining financial integrity, supporting professional growth, and fostering transparency through standardized governance and communication frameworks.</p>\n  <ul class=\"efg-pillars\">\n    <li>Accounting</li>\n    <li>Treasury</li>\n    <li>Tax & Transfer Pricing</li>\n    <li>Controlling, FP&A</li>\n    <li>Procurement</li>\n  </ul>\n</section>",
                "Division": "Finance",
                "Extra": "<section itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/CreativeWork\">\n  <h2 itemprop=\"name\">Finance Division Extra Information</h2>\n  <p itemprop=\"description\">Additional resources, governance frameworks, and operational guidelines for the EFG Finance division.</p>\n\n  <h3>Finance Governance & Communication</h3>\n  <p>The Finance division maintains a structured framework for decision-making and information flow to ensure transparency and clarity. This includes:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Communication Guidelines:</strong> Standards for internal updates and reporting.</li>\n    <li><strong>Department Townhall Meetings:</strong> Quarterly sessions for company announcements, guest speakers, and celebrating achievements.</li>\n    <li><strong>Leadership Pulse:</strong> Monthly meetings for L1-3 leadership focused on strategic alignment and escalation handling.</li>\n    <li><strong>Initiative Sync:</strong> Monthly operational meetings for L3 and below to track project progress via Jira and highlight successes.</li>\n    <li><strong>Functional Tactical:</strong> Team-specific meetings to align on day-to-day priorities and workload management.</li>\n    <li><strong>Weekly 1:1s:</strong> Mandatory weekly meetings between managers and their direct reports.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>Master Data Framework</h3>\n  <p>Finance manages a central repository for Finance-Owned Master Data, which serves as the single source of truth for reporting, budgeting, and compliance. The framework covers the lifecycle of data points, including:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Creation:</strong> Intake and onboarding of new data points.</li>\n    <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Ongoing updates to ensure accuracy.</li>\n    <li><strong>Management:</strong> Overarching governance and security of the datasets.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>Standardized Templates</h3>\n  <p>To ensure consistency, the Finance division utilizes standardized templates for documentation, including Policies, Guidelines, SOPs, Process Descriptions, and RACM files. These are managed by Charlotta Hjalmarsson.</p>\n\n  <h3>Service Exceptions</h3>\n  <p>Certain services are managed outside of standard procurement workflows due to their nature or regulatory requirements:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Freelancers:</strong> Managed by the Division based on professional expertise.</li>\n    <li><strong>Audit Companies:</strong> Appointed directly by the ARC.</li>\n    <li><strong>Legal Advisors:</strong> Controlled by the Legal department.</li>\n    <li><strong>Property Taxes & Public Charges:</strong> Managed by Finance as unavoidable costs.</li>\n    <li><strong>Employee Benefits:</strong> Managed by HR (e.g., health insurance).</li>\n    <li><strong>Governmental Services:</strong> Managed based on the specific service (e.g., France Travail, medical checks).</li>\n    <li><strong>Banking Services:</strong> Managed by Finance.</li>\n    <li><strong>Finance Advisors:</strong> Managed by Finance under spend management.</li>\n    <li><strong>EOR / Payroll Services:</strong> Managed by HR / US ops team.</li>\n    <li><strong>Advertisement Services:</strong> Managed by Marketing.</li>\n    <li><strong>Players/Teams:</strong> Managed by Esports (e.g., BootCamp, merchandise).</li>\n  </ul>\n</section>",
